There need not be upper lip, could be pride.

957
01:07:55,880 --> 01:08:03,400
[Yogi’s laugh and one make an indistinct comment at which Shri Mataji laughs]

958
01:08:03,800 --> 01:08:07,960
Shri Mataji: That kind of a presence is here, [INDISTINCT: DOUR,]

959
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:10,160
which is specialty of English also, isn’t it?

960
01:08:10,241 --> 01:08:13,732
You go in a train, they just don’t talk. I mean they don’t allow you to talk,

961
01:08:13,813 --> 01:08:17,999
they freeze you with silence.

962
01:08:18,120 --> 01:08:20,440
They can’t see people laugh, smile or joke,

963
01:08:20,680 --> 01:08:24,360
anything a …[SILENCE] and you don’t know what to do with them.

964
01:08:24,600 --> 01:08:26,999
Newspaper they will read only all the way,

965
01:08:27,160 --> 01:08:30,720
and they will fold it and read it.

966
01:08:30,801 --> 01:08:33,505
But they know each and everything about you.

967
01:08:33,586 --> 01:08:36,960
Yogini: Could it be called “insular.”

968
01:08:37,000 --> 01:08:41,960
Shri Mataji: Insular. Ah yes! And is a very dangerous thing for Sahaj Yogis.

969
01:08:42,000 --> 01:08:47,040
The one who becomes insular is in for trouble.

970
01:08:47,440 --> 01:08:50,200
Is in for trouble, insular.

971
01:08:50,440 --> 01:08:54,200
You know why, because you are left alone, you’ll be attacked.

972
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:59,480
Be together. All these bhoots also know you are insular.

973
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:02,640
They’ll attack you.

974
01:09:02,960 --> 01:09:06,560
By any chance you try to become unique, they’ll attack you.

975
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:07,999
Even some people become,

976
01:09:08,120 --> 01:09:11,680
by talking too much also they can become insular, unique;

977
01:09:11,920 --> 01:09:18,240
you sit on top of everybody else. Better be with everyone, is better.

978
01:09:19,520 --> 01:09:21,560
Be one with everybody, congenial.

979
01:09:21,800 --> 01:09:22,999
Take a joke from others.

980
01:09:23,200 --> 01:09:25,760
Other are joking with you, you should not get angry.

981
01:09:25,841 --> 01:09:27,918
If somebody joking with you, “Oh! Shut up.”

982
01:09:27,999 --> 01:09:32,440
Like that one should not do. Take a joke, be a sport.

983
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:34,999
English language has one very good quality

984
01:09:35,200 --> 01:09:38,320
that they can laugh at themselves, you see. All the

985
01:09:38,640 --> 01:09:42,960
language has found out ways and methods of how to laugh at yourself,

986
01:09:43,000 --> 01:09:46,320
that’s something beautiful about English language.

987
01:09:46,560 --> 01:09:49,360
I don’t think any language has so many words

988
01:09:49,600 --> 01:09:52,999
to express these odd situations,

989
01:09:53,080 --> 01:09:57,280
which are very, very embarrassing you see.

990
01:09:57,840 --> 01:10:02,320
You can only brand them and by branding them, you know where you are.

991
01:10:02,560 --> 01:10:05,080
You exactly know what medicine is needed for this.

992
01:10:05,320 --> 01:10:06,560
You see it is like that.

993
01:10:06,800 --> 01:10:08,960
It’s just branding, “Oh this is it,”

994
01:10:09,000 --> 01:10:11,999
and it’s very interesting to watch these things

995
01:10:12,080 --> 01:10:13,719
in the society and everywhere.

996
01:10:13,800 --> 01:10:16,280
Which is described, even Charles Dickens, now example,

997
01:10:16,361 --> 01:10:18,319
at that time he found out these things

998
01:10:18,400 --> 01:10:22,160
and he said it. And I mean the description of all these things is

999
01:10:22,520 --> 01:10:27,160
so beautifully done in the literature that you are amazed how people

1000
01:10:27,400 --> 01:10:29,040
had a capacity to see themselves,

1001
01:10:29,280 --> 01:10:33,600
the society as it is and to de… Characterization of people:

1002
01:10:33,840 --> 01:10:35,720
how characters are built up you see

1003
01:10:35,960 --> 01:10:37,720
and how it becomes a social problem.

1004
01:10:37,960 --> 01:10:39,440
It’s beautifully done

1005
01:10:39,680 --> 01:10:44,840
and that’s the wisdom. That’s the real wisdom of British, I tell you

1006
01:10:44,999 --> 01:10:46,280
I mean you may lose it

1007
01:10:46,520 --> 01:10:49,200
if you start getting dominated by nonsensical ideas,

1008
01:10:49,440 --> 01:10:51,520
but otherwise that wisdom you have innate.

1009
01:10:51,760 --> 01:10:54,680
I mean to have a person like Shakespeare itself shows what?

1010
01:10:54,999 --> 01:10:58,480
I mean you are a country of great people. How can that be?

1011
01:10:58,720 --> 01:11:03,080
Where some, they are not  “some,” there are quite a lot of them

1012
01:11:03,320 --> 01:11:05,320
and you are going to be the wisest

1013
01:11:05,560 --> 01:11:08,320
because you have the advantage of their creation.

1014
01:11:08,999 --> 01:11:12,640
On top of, you have got advantage of your creation.

1015
01:11:12,880 --> 01:11:15,199
Then/that? you belong to a great country like that.

1016
01:11:15,280 --> 01:11:19,960
Imagine the whole country is getting into the mire of lethargy,

1017
01:11:20,000 --> 01:11:21,563
who is going to save this country?

1018
01:11:21,644 --> 01:11:28,320
You people. So again and again it is against lethargy

1019
01:11:28,999 --> 01:11:33,999
and whatever is lethargy is anti Christ,

1020
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:38,999
is anti God, is anti Mataji.

1021
01:11:40,999 --> 01:11:45,320
Try to become cheerful and blissful,

1022
01:11:45,560 --> 01:11:51,120
happy, dignified, sensible, sweet.

1023
01:11:52,480 --> 01:11:57,400
It’s not too many things, is very few, it’s only one.

1024
01:11:57,640 --> 01:12:01,760
And I know we are going to enjoy life very much.

1025
01:12:01,999 --> 01:12:04,480
You are going to be very happy people.

1026
01:12:04,760 --> 01:12:08,960
Take out your tempers from your heads first of all, the angers you see

1027
01:12:09,000 --> 01:12:13,280
and to say, “I got very angry.” Means what? Why did you get angry?

1028
01:12:13,520 --> 01:12:18,240
To be proud of your anger and temper and your irritations!

1029
01:12:18,480 --> 01:12:21,240
It will be very beautiful I am sure. You are growing up,

1030
01:12:21,760 --> 01:12:23,999
but the growth becomes little

1031
01:12:24,320 --> 01:12:27,600
dwarfed with these nonsensical things, you know.

1032
01:12:27,840 --> 01:12:30,760
So you have to protect your growth from these things

1033
01:12:30,999 --> 01:12:35,999
as we protect a small plant from say frost falling on a plant.

1034
01:12:36,160 --> 01:12:37,280
It’s like that.

1035
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:40,960
Frost is nothing compared to the plant, because plant is growing,

1036
01:12:41,000 --> 01:12:44,840
but the frost can kill it and that’s how you do not make it a frost.

1037
01:12:44,999 --> 01:12:45,960
Be cheerful.

1038
01:12:46,120 --> 01:12:48,960
People come up and they go down. I’ve seen people come up

1039
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:51,960
and then they go down. Try to look after yourself.

1040
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:54,960
Now after seventeen days I am going to come and see you

1041
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:58,080
very beautifully developed and all the time My attention is on you,

1042
01:12:58,320 --> 01:13:00,160
I work on you all the time.

1043
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:07,520
And I’m much more intimate with you than with anybody else,

1044
01:13:07,760 --> 01:13:09,999
because these people see Me only for two days

1045
01:13:10,200 --> 01:13:13,280
and then they started crying!

1046
01:13:13,600 --> 01:13:19,999
They’re lost. But I see you so much, more than even Indians.

1047
01:13:21,120 --> 01:13:24,760
Is Paul there? Paul has come?

1048
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:26,960
Yogi: Yes Mother.

1049
01:13:27,000 --> 01:13:32,520
Shri Mataji: Yes. Hm. Paul, what happened?

1050
01:13:32,672 --> 01:13:36,999
Paul: I want to get a message to, from the people of India… Shri Mataji: Ha?

1051
01:13:37,080 --> 01:13:39,855
Paul: …Apart from the – the people of India send their love.

1052
01:13:39,936 --> 01:13:43,560
But one of the Sahaj Yogis in india has become very ill.

1053
01:13:43,641 --> 01:13:46,291
Shri Mataji: Who? Paul: Professor [INDISTINCT: Manneh] in Rahur.

1054
01:13:46,372 --> 01:13:50,320
Shri Mataji: I know. But why did you get angry with Dhumal?

1055
01:13:50,600 --> 01:13:55,240
Paul: Dhumal? By that time I’d really, I’d

1056
01:13:55,680 --> 01:13:57,920
had enough of seeing in India the way that

1057
01:13:58,000 --> 01:13:59,800
there’s two classes of people in India:

1058
01:13:59,999 --> 01:14:02,240
those who have a lot of money and those who–

1059
01:14:02,680 --> 01:14:04,999
Shri Mataji: And what about in this country?

1060
01:14:05,080 --> 01:14:07,199
Paul: Well it’s the same deal in this country,

1061
01:14:07,280 --> 01:14:09,960
but the people in this country who don’t have a lot of money,

1062
01:14:10,041 --> 01:14:11,880
at least they have bare necessities of life.

1063
01:14:11,961 --> 01:14:13,421
You know like a roof over their heads.

1064
01:14:13,502 --> 01:14:17,622
Shri Mataji: You went there to do Sahaj Yoga or to do these things?

1065
01:14:17,800 --> 01:14:20,280
You see, what I’m saying, where was your attention?

1066
01:14:20,520 --> 01:14:25,999
Now you knows, Dhumal has given realizations to ten thousand people.

1067
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:30,960
And he’s your elder brother, you should respect him.

1068
01:14:31,320 --> 01:14:34,960
He has a servant, because in India the situation is different.

1069
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:37,999
If he gives up his servant, he’ll have no food to eat.

1070
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:40,999
It’s not that everybody use brain.

1071
01:14:41,160 --> 01:14:44,245
You see this is one thing in this country people do not realize.

1072
01:14:44,326 --> 01:14:48,240
If you use, you work much harder than his servant, do you know that?

1073
01:14:48,480 --> 01:14:51,440
Because your brain never stops.

1074
01:14:51,760 --> 01:14:55,160
His servants works with his hand he doesn’t think!

1075
01:14:55,480 --> 01:14:58,960
His energy goes to his hands, he rests also.

1076
01:14:59,000 --> 01:15:02,120
You see here the idea is if somebody’s working with the hand,

1077
01:15:02,360 --> 01:15:03,000
it’s cruelty.

1078
01:15:03,240 --> 01:15:05,800
But what about this brain?

1079
01:15:06,200 --> 01:15:09,120
The amount of brain you use all the time – now tell me,

1080
01:15:09,360 --> 01:15:11,840
you cannot stop your thinking, all right?

1081
01:15:11,999 --> 01:15:13,800
Now see My servant,

1082
01:15:13,999 --> 01:15:17,999
though he works hard, he’s much more relaxed than My husband is.

1083
01:15:18,160 --> 01:15:23,880
My husband doesn’t do even lifting a, say lifting a glass.

1084
01:15:23,999 --> 01:15:25,240
All right?

1085
01:15:25,480 --> 01:15:29,000
And what happens, that one can say that this man is a lazy fellow,

1086
01:15:29,240 --> 01:15:30,800
he’s enjoying everything in life,

1087
01:15:30,999 --> 01:15:33,999
he’s enjoying all the comfort while the servant is not.

1088
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:37,320
But My servant is, in a way, is doing his handwork,

1089
01:15:37,560 --> 01:15:40,520
because that’s all he can do; his brain is not that developed.

1090
01:15:40,760 --> 01:15:43,999
And he has much more rest than My husband has.

1091
01:15:44,080 --> 01:15:46,760
He’s much more relaxed.

1092
01:15:47,120 --> 01:15:51,440
Somebody is the hand, somebody is the feet and somebody’s the head.

1093
01:15:51,680 --> 01:15:54,480
But if you do work with your head, is the same.

1094
01:15:54,561 --> 01:15:56,519
Now if you are doing work with your head,

1095
01:15:56,600 --> 01:16:00,000
you have to have certain amount of comfort to your body,

1096
01:16:00,240 --> 01:16:02,960
otherwise even if you have to suffer on your body –

1097
01:16:03,000 --> 01:16:05,520
of course I do not say that servants

1098
01:16:05,760 --> 01:16:07,440
should be ill-treated by any chance,

1099
01:16:07,680 --> 01:16:11,200
that should not be done – but…

1100
01:16:11,600 --> 01:16:14,120
And nobody gives your money to anybody else like that.

1101
01:16:14,360 --> 01:16:15,520
You see he’s paid for it

1102
01:16:15,760 --> 01:16:18,280
and he does the work with his hands so you can see it.

1103
01:16:18,520 --> 01:16:24,520
But what about the brain part, do you see the brain how it works?

1104
01:16:24,760 --> 01:16:28,400
I wish you could have a microscope to see how the brain works,

1105
01:16:28,640 --> 01:16:31,440
and all the chakras, “cutcutcutcut-cutcutcutcut” going on.

1106
01:16:31,680 --> 01:16:39,080
One thought itself is a dynamite

1107
01:16:39,600 --> 01:16:41,080
and you cannot stop it, ask him.

1108
01:16:41,320 --> 01:16:44,240
Yesterday his thought going on like a machine!

1109
01:16:44,480 --> 01:16:46,200
There’s a machine here working out.

1110
01:16:46,440 --> 01:16:48,960
So, this happens and then one should understand

1111
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:51,080
that when you go to any country,

1112
01:16:51,360 --> 01:16:53,640
you are a guest there…

1113
01:16:53,960 --> 01:16:57,400
He was very unhappy and he wrote a very sad letter to Me

1114
01:16:57,760 --> 01:17:00,960
and that was not good. You didn’t want him to be unhappy, you w–

1115
01:17:01,000 --> 01:17:02,960
Paul: What if I write? Shri Mataji: Ha? Dhumal?

1116
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:04,960
Paul: We didn’t have an argument. Shri Mataji: Ha?

1117
01:17:05,000 --> 01:17:06,960
Paul: I didn’t have an argument. Shri Mataji: You didn’t have what?

1118
01:17:07,000 --> 01:17:07,960
Paul: I told him what I felt. Shri Mataji: Ha?

1119
01:17:08,000 --> 01:17:11,280
Paul: I told him what I felt, I just went, I just… you know the most,

1120
01:17:11,520 --> 01:17:15,000
quite a lot of places in India. And–

1121
01:17:15,240 --> 01:17:16,960
Shri Mataji: You, what did you feel?

1122
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:21,720
Paul: Well I felt that if somebody’s telling me how many houses they’ve got

1123
01:17:21,999 --> 01:17:26,960
and how many houses they’re buying, when their servant doesn’t have a roof over his head,

1124
01:17:27,000 --> 01:17:28,960
when the roof leaks and the children–

1125
01:17:29,000 --> 01:17:32,960
Shri Mataji: Now, supposing, here people have so many houses which are lying empty, here,

1126
01:17:33,000 --> 01:17:37,680
in England. Do they give their houses to you people?

1127
01:17:37,920 --> 01:17:39,960
Do they? Is there any way?

1128
01:17:40,000 --> 01:17:44,960
How many people you should give also, is there any system by which you should give?

1129
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:50,960
See that is not Dhumal’s problem, is the problem of the government.

1130
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:57,960
Dhumal has houses, he has given a huge big fort to us as a present to Sahaj Yoga.

1131
01:17:58,000 --> 01:18:03,960
If he gives a house free to his servant, I think he will make him a parasite out of him.

1132
01:18:04,000 --> 01:18:08,960
Do you know in India, beggars have got big, big buildings? Do you know that fact?

1133
01:18:09,000 --> 01:18:16,960
Some of the buildings on Marine Drive are owned by people who are professionally beggars.

1134
01:18:17,000 --> 01:18:21,960
So if you see some problem it has so many deeper roots, which you do not see.

1135
01:18:22,000 --> 01:18:26,960
But, you just write a letter of apology to him. I was hurt, very much,

1136
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:32,960
because he, he has done such a tremendous job.

1137
01:18:33,000 --> 01:18:38,960
He is going to give a huge big place to us for Sahaj Yoga.

1138
01:18:39,000 --> 01:18:42,960
Nobody has been able to do that so far.

1139
01:18:43,000 --> 01:18:49,960
He has given Me ten thousand people as Sahaj Yogis. And when you people say,

1140
01:18:50,000 --> 01:18:58,960
“I felt,” what is this “I,” what is this “I”? I know you have a very sympathetic heart,

1141
01:18:59,000 --> 01:19:05,960
but sometimes you are swayed by it. Sympathetic heart, to a point is good.

1142
01:19:06,000 --> 01:19:08,960
It should be prudent heart, it should not be unwise.

1143
01:19:09,000 --> 01:19:10,960
You must know the sense of proportion.

1144
01:19:11,000 --> 01:19:14,960
I mean that’s a system in India, which is working, but you cannot do without servants.

1145
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:19,960
Here also. What is happening to you, without servants, you are all intelligent people,

1146
01:19:20,000 --> 01:19:22,960
why you live in a mess, in pigsties?

1147
01:19:23,000 --> 01:19:25,960
Because you are using your brains, you don’t know how to use your hands.

1148
01:19:26,000 --> 01:19:31,960
All these communistic ideas are of no use. People have to do some sort of a job,

1149
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:36,960
this job or that job. There’s nothing wrong. Some people who can do brain job,

1150
01:19:37,000 --> 01:19:39,960
have to do brain job, those who have to do handwork has to do handwork.

1151
01:19:40,000 --> 01:19:43,960
Of course there should not be much disparity in their living, I agree,

1152
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:48,960
but that’s not his problem, is the problem of the whole country.

1153
01:19:49,000 --> 01:19:52,960
But I tell you even to servants I have seen, you give them something…

1154
01:19:53,000 --> 01:19:55,960
There was a lady nurse, you see?

1155
01:19:56,000 --> 01:20:00,960
Once I was rather sick so she used to come and see Me and help Me a little bit.

1156
01:20:01,000 --> 01:20:03,960
So I thought just as a favor I must do something to her.

1157
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:09,960
So I sent her by our ship to sea, I said “Let her have a holiday, she’ll be all right.”

1158
01:20:10,000 --> 01:20:14,960
So I sent her to Africa. I mean the problems are much deeper than you understand.

1159
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:19,960
I sent her to Africa. You know, she came back and she started telling the doctor off.

1160
01:20:20,000 --> 01:20:21,960
She thought she has become the doctor.

1161
01:20:22,000 --> 01:20:25,960
And the doctor told Me, “Why did you do it?” They get into imbalances. You see,

1162
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:32,960
even to poor persons, if you give them something like that, they go into imbalances.

1163
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:35,960
I’ll give you another very concrete example.

1164
01:20:36,000 --> 01:20:40,960
My husband, who is very socialistic in his approach, and is a good thing,

1165
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:43,960
so what he did, was to increase the pay of the drivers.

1166
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:47,960
You see the drivers started getting one thousand Rupee, which was very, very big amount.

1167
01:20:48,000 --> 01:20:50,960
And the lowest clerk gets about say twelve hundred.

1168
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:53,960
So there was a very little disparity.

1169
01:20:54,000 --> 01:20:57,960
Now the driver’s getting one thousand Rupees, was too much.

1170
01:20:58,000 --> 01:20:59,960
Within six months their wives came to Me.

1171
01:21:00,000 --> 01:21:03,960
They said, “This was a very wrong thing he did to our husbands.

1172
01:21:04,000 --> 01:21:06,960
They have got keeps now; they have started drinking;

1173
01:21:07,000 --> 01:21:10,960
they have started not giving any money to us.”

1174
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:13,960
So to poor people if you give them more money,

1175
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:17,960
they do not know how to use it, they will be drinking.

1176
01:21:18,000 --> 01:21:20,960
Poor people drink much more than the rich people.

1177
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:28,960
So they had to be trained how to use money. You just give them money is no use.

1178
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:35,960
You do not understand the deeper… thing… People are to be brought up properly.

1179
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:39,960
Like we have got in India Schedule Caste – I agree Schedule Caste is a nonsense,

1180
01:21:40,000 --> 01:21:43,960
it should not be there, you should not treat somebody as a lower caste, is all right.

1181
01:21:44,000 --> 01:21:46,960
But what they have brought into now, suddenly,

1182
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:52,960
that Schedule Caste must have equal seats, equal rights in every job and everything,

1183
